description.p:
Accordingly, the present invention relates to:
[1] a method of measuring the degree of stress excluding inflammatory stress, which comprises measuring an increase in the amount or activity of IL-18 and an increase in the activity of P3 8MAP kinase using an IL-18 antibody and a P38MAP kinase antibody as a visualizing agent, wherein the amount or activity of IL-18 is measured in adrenal tissue or blood collected from an animal and the activity of P38MAP kinase is measured in adrenal tissue collected from an animal;
[2] the method described in [1], wherein the IL-18 is active type IL-18 present in blood, the amount or activity of IL-18 in blood is measured and/or the P38MAP kinase is phosphorylated kinase;
[3] the method described in [2], wherein the P38MAP kinase is derived from a mouse, and the phosphorylation site of the kinase is Thr180 or Tyr182, or the P38MAP kinase is derived from a human, and the phosphorylation site of the kinase is Thr185 or Tyr187;
[4] the method described in any one of [1] to [3], wherein the stress is mental stress, optionally restraint stress;
[5] the method of described in any one of [1] to [4], wherein the animal is a human;
[6] use of a visualizing agent which comprises an IL-18 antibody and a visualizing agent which comprises a P38MAP kinase antibody in detecting a response to stress excluding inflammatory stress by detecting an increase in the amount or activity of IL-18 and an increase in the activity of P38MAP kinase, wherein the amount or activity of IL-18 is detected in blood or adrenal tissue collected from an animal and the activity of P38MAP kinase is detected in adrenal tissue collected from an animal;
[7] the use of [6], wherein the IL-18 antibody specifically recognizes active type IL-18 and/or the P38MAP kinase antibody is an anti-phosphorylated P38MAP kinase antibody;
[8] the use of [7], wherein the anti-phosphorylated P38MAP kinase antibody recognizes a P38MAP kinase having phosphorylated Thr180 or Tyr182, or a P38MAP kinase having phosphorylated Thr185 or Tyr187;
[9] use of a kit in a method of measuring stress excluding inflammatory stress described in any one of [1] to [5], which kit comprises the visualizing agents described in any one of [6] to [8];
[10] a method of screening for a substance having a therapeutic effect, ameliorating effect or prophylactic effect on a disease that occurs, exacerbates or recurs due to mental stress, which comprises:
1) quantifying the amount or activity of IL-18 in adrenal tissue or blood collected from an animal and the activity of P38MAP kinase in adrenal tissue collected from the animal;
2) comparing the amount or activity of said IL-18 and the activity of said P38MAP kinase in the presence and absence of the test substance; and
3) judging that a test substance that reduces or increases the amount or activity of IL-18 and the activity of P38MAP kinase is a substance having a therapeutic effect, ameliorating effect or prophylactic effect on a disease that occurs, exacerbates or recurs due to mental stress; optionally wherein the disease is systemic lupus erythematosus, lupus nephritis, atopic dermatitis, multiple sclerosis, bronchial asthma, psoriasis, cerebral ischemia, cerebral degeneration, encephalitis, articular rheumatism, emmeniopathy, endometriosis or sexual desire reduction;
[11] a method of screening for a substance having a suppressive effect or preventive effect on oxidative stress, which comprises:
1) quantifying the amount or activity of IL-18 in adrenal tissue or blood collected from an animal and the activity of P38MAP kinase in adrenal tissue collected from the animal;
2) comparing the amount or activity of said IL-18 and the activity of said P38MAP kinase in the presence and absence of the test substance; and
3) judging that a test substance that reduces or increases the amount or activity of IL-18 and the activity of P38MAP kinase is a substance having a suppressive effect or preventative effect on oxidative stress; and
[12] the method described in [10] or [11], wherein the IL-18 is active-type IL-18 and/or the P38MAP kinase is phosphorylated kinase.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren zum Screening nach einer Substanz mit einer therapeutischen Wirkung, lindernden Wirkung oder prophylaktischen Wirkung auf eine Krankheit, die aufgrund von mentalem Stress auftritt, sich verschlimmert oder zurückkehrt, umfassend:
1) Quantifizieren der Menge oder Aktivität von IL-18 in Nebennierengewebe oder Blut, das von einem Tier gesammelt wird, und der Aktivität von P38MAP-Kinase in Nebennierengewebe, das von einem Tier gesammelt wird;
2) Vergleichen der Menge oder Aktivität des IL-18 und der Aktivität der P38MAP-Kinase in Anwesenheit und Abwesenheit der Testsubstanz; und
3) Beurteilen, dass eine Testsubstanz, die die Menge oder Aktivität von IL-18 und die Aktivität von P38MAP-Kinase reduziert oder erhöht, eine Substanz mit einer therapeutischen Wirkung, lindernden Wirkung oder prophylaktischen Wirkung auf eine Krankheit, die aufgrund von mentalem Stress auftritt, sich verschlimmert oder zurückkehrt, ist;
wobei es sich bei der Krankheit gegebenenfalls um systemischen Lupus erythematodes, Lupus nephritis, atopische Dermatitis, multiple Sklerose, Bronchialasthma, Psoriasis, Hirnblutung, Hirndegeneration, Enzephalitis, Gelenkrheumatismus, Menstruationsstörungen, Endometriose oder sexuelle Appetenzstörung handelt.
